      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SNIPPY WHICH (1) progressed again beaten a head over 1200m at Ascot in a 66. Was doing his best work late and keeps the handy 2kg claim. Has the talent and is well placed to go one better. SNOW GOD (5) tracked the speed in the same race but didn't finish it off. He'd resumed prior at Ascot heavily bet, and it was a solid effort over shorter. He's right up to this at best, and Paul Harvey on his return to race riding is in the saddle. ZING TO WIN (3) had been knocking on the door before a plainer run at Bunbury when he was well out of the market. Maps well and the 3kg claim brings him into it. Could surprise. MIGHTY HOSANNA (9) runs along and resumed with a near miss here, followed by a CL3 win this trip at Scarpside. Expect that to stack up, and she will be fitter again. The free-running SHOWLAS (7) resumes and flies fresh. Has numbers good enough for this, and she's trialled well at Lark Hill. Keep onside.",
